items.title: Phase retrieval - Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
items.htmlTitle: Phase retrieval - Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
items.snippet:
The error reduction is a generalisation of the Gerchberg–Saxton algorithm. It 
solves for f(x) from measurements of |F(x)| . It uses iteration of a four-step process.

items.htmlTitle: Adaptive-additive algorithm - Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
items.snippet:
Increase loop by one n \to n + 1 and repeat. Limits[edit]. If a = 1 then the AA 
algorithm becomes the Gerchberg–Saxton algorithm. If a = 0 then \bar{A}^k_n = 
A_0 .
